w.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fgodrej-properties-q2fy25-result-pat-jumps-5-fold-to-rs-335-21-crore-124102300679_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22America%20needs%20more%20weird%20homes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20block%20homes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6717ab7b01ea6d83dee316fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMikel%20Jaso%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere's%20a%20classic%20joke%20about%20two%20old%20ladies%20complaining%20that%20a%20local%20restaurant%20has%20terrible%20food%20%E2%80%94%20and%20portions%20that%20are%20way%20too%20small.%20You%20could%20say%20something%20similar%20about%20housing%20in%20much%20of%20the%20United%20States%3A%20The%20homes%20on%20offer%20are%20dull%2C%20uninspiring%2C%20nearly%20identical%2C%20and%20in%20far%20too%20short%20supply.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20cookie-cutter%20sameness%20of%20American%20abodes%20and%20the%20worrying%20lack%20of%20new%20construction%20seem%20like%20two%20distinct%20issues%2C%20they%20actually%20go%20hand%20in%20hand.%20Local%20building%20codes%20and%20other%20land-use%20regulations%20have%20imposed%20strict%20limits%20on%20the%20size%20and%20shape%20of%20new%20housing%2C%20leading%20to%20both%20a%20major%20supply%20crunch%20and%20a%20deadening%20aesthetic%20uniformity%20of%20the%20housing%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Edoes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20get%20built.%20On%20most%20residential%20land%2C%20developers%20can%20legally%20build%20only%20detached%20single-family%20housing%20%E2%80%94%20usually%20with%20a%20big%20yard%20out%20front.%20While%20there's%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20wanting%20to%20live%20in%20that%20housing%2C%20people%20who%20prefer%20something%20different%20have%20few%20options.%20And%20in%20high-demand%20areas%2C%20working-class%20and%20low-income%20people%20increasingly%20have%20no%20options%20at%20all.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20this%20way.%20The%20single-family%20home%20need%20not%20be%20the%20sole%20legal%20construction%20option.%20If%20we%20introduce%20more%20flexibility%20into%20the%20design%20rules%20for%20housing%20construction%2C%20we%20could%20end%20up%20with%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20housing%20across%20our%20cities%20%E2%80%94%20something%20for%20everyone%20to%20meet%20every%20household's%20needs.%20We%20have%20the%20power%20to%20make%20homes%20weird%20again.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c01429e9-1d1c-42ea-87d6-565ca37e8a96%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20history%20of%20sameness%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20years%20following%20World%20War%20II%2C%20the%20sameness%20of%20American%20housing%20was%20part%20of%20what%20fueled%20the%20boom%20in%20new%20home%20construction%20that%20turned%20the%20country%20into%20a%20homeownership%20society.%20In%20the%20planned%20community%20of%20Levittown%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20its%20imitators%2C%20developers%20quickly%20assembled%20thousands%20of%20nearly%20identical%20single-family%20homes%20for%20returning%20GIs%20and%20their%20families.%20Because%20these%20homes%20were%20so%20similar%2C%20builders%20could%20mass-produce%20them%20with%20prefabricated%20materials%2C%20almost%20as%20if%20they%20were%203D%20printing%20an%20entire%20community%20from%20one%20set%20of%20floor%20plans.%20Though%20this%20homogeneity%20would%20later%20invite%20disdain%20%E2%80%94%20see%20the%201962%20song%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgenius.com%2FMalvina-reynolds-little-boxes-lyrics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ELittle%20Boxes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20it%20held%20down%20construction%20costs%2C%20which%20allowed%20developers%20to%20offer%20the%20homes%20for%20sale%20to%20young%20families%20at%20affordable%20prices.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20trouble%20started%20in%20the%20latter%20half%20of%20the%2020th%20century%20because%20cities%20decided%20to%20enforce%20that%20sameness.%20Instead%20of%20letting%20developers%20build%20the%20type%20of%20housing%20best%20suited%20for%20an%20area%2C%20many%20cities%20set%20a%20normative%20standard%20that%20the%20detached%20single-family%20home%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20home%20for%20everyone%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20income%2C%20preferences%2C%20and%20family%20configuration.%20And%20when%20local%20governments%20insist%20that%20this%20is%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eonly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20type%20of%20housing%20one%20can%20legally%20build%20in%20most%20of%20the%20city%2C%20they%20limit%20how%20many%20residents%20that%20city%20can%20comfortably%20accommodate.%20Take%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20where%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbelonging.berkeley.edu%2Fsingle-family-zoning-greater-los-angeles%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20about%20three-quarters%20of%20residential-zoned%20land%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202021%20was%20zoned%20exclusively%20for%20developing%20single-family%20housing.%20The%20results%20have%20been%20predictable%3A%20LA%20has%20a%20severe%20housing%20shortage%2C%20a%20devastating%20homelessness%20crisis%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fcalifornia%2Fstory%2F2022-10-19%2Flos-angeles-history-overcrowding-united-states%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20worst%20overcrowding%20in%20the%20country%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20local%20governments%20go%20beyond%20the%20single-family-house%20mandate%20and%20set%20strict%20rules%20regarding%20the%20design%20of%20the%20house%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20parking%20space%20in%20each%20garage%2C%20and%20even%20the%20size%20of%20the%20lot%20on%20which%20the%20house%20sits.%20The%20website%20for%20the%20pro-housing%20group%20Desegregate%20Connecticut%20says%20that%20%26quot%3B81%25%20of%20residential%20land%20in%20Connecticut%20requires%20about%201%20acre%20per%20home%2C%20and%2049%25%20requires%20about%202%20acres%20per%20home%20(a%20football%20field%20and%20a%20half!).%26quot%3B%20That%20means%20the%20Levittown%20homes%2C%20which%20sit%20on%206%2C000-square-foot%20lots%2C%20would%20be%20illegal%20to%20build%20in%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20Connecticut.%20Even%20in%20the%20rare%20spots%20where%20developers%20are%20allowed%20to%20build%20multifamily%20housing%2C%20they're%20often%20strictly%20limited%20in%20the%20type%20of%20apartments%20they%20can%20build.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2F22650806%2Fgentrification-affordable-housing-low-income-housing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emuch-loathed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%205-over-1%20apartment%20building%20became%20so%20prevalent%20in%20part%20because%20it%20conforms%20to%20objective%20design%20standards%2C%20minimum%20parking%20requirements%2C%20and%20the%20common%20legal%20requirement%20that%20multifamily%20buildings%20over%20a%20certain%20size%20have%20multiple%20staircases.%20These%20rules%20make%20apartment%20buildings%20larger%20than%20they%20need%20to%20be%20and%20unnecessarily%20expensive%20to%20build.%20Plus%2C%20they%20can%20be%20built%20with%20only%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20floor%20plans%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20to%20include%20%26quot%3Bfamily-sized%26quot%3B%20apartments%20with%20three%20or%20more%20bedrooms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20country%20needs%20to%20build%20more%20homes%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20reason%20all%20those%20new%20homes%20need%20to%20look%20the%20same.%20In%20fact%2C%20we'll%20get%20a%20lot%20more%20of%20the%20housing%20we%20need%20if%20we%20allow%20for%20more%20experimentation%20with%20housing%20types%20in%20our%20cities.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20we%20need%20to%20let%20homebuilders%20get%20a%20little%20weird.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2218cd0803-db22-4ce9-840b-05b66237213e%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWeird%20is%20good%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20a%20sense%20of%20what%20%26quot%3Bweird%26quot%3B%20could%20look%20like%2C%20look%20at%20metropolitan%20Tokyo%2C%20a%20region%20that%20has%20done%20an%20excellent%20job%20of%20controlling%20housing%20costs%20even%20as%20its%20population%20has%20nearly%20quadrupled%20since%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20II.%20Tokyo%20has%20homes%20in%20all%20shapes%20and%20sizes%3A%20detached%20single-family%20homes%2C%20attached%20row%20houses%2C%20small%20apartment%20buildings%2C%20midsize%20apartment%20buildings%2C%20and%20colossal%20residential%20high-rises.%20Spend%20some%20time%20in%20the%20area%20and%20you'll%20notice%20that%20these%20homes%20also%20come%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20architectural%20styles%20%E2%80%94%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20enforced%20uniformity%20of%20many%20American%20cities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere's%20a%20reason%20for%20all%20that%20heterogeneity%3A%20Unlike%20nearly%20every%20American%20city%2C%20Tokyo%20has%20a%20loose%20approach%20to%20land-use%20regulation.%20An%20American%20city%20may%20have%20hundreds%20of%20zoning%20classifications%2C%20but%20the%20entire%20country%20of%20Japan%20has%20only%20a%20baker's%20dozen%3A%20eight%20residential%20zones%2C%20two%20commercial%20zones%2C%20and%20three%20industrial%20zones.%20This%20zoning%20is%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20organized%20vertically%3A%20Any%20lot%20that%20permits%20a%20certain%20type%20of%20use%20also%20allows%20other%20uses%20of%20equal%20or%20lower%20intensity.%20For%20instance%2C%20it%20is%20legal%20to%20build%20a%20house%2C%20or%20a%20house%20with%20a%20small%20attached%20shop%2C%20on%20most%20lots%2C%20except%20for%20certain%20industrial%20ones.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20rules%20do%20not%20come%20with%20the%20arbitrary%20aesthetic%20standards%20you%20find%20in%20many%20American%20cities.%20But%20instead%20of%20being%20chaotic%2C%20Tokyo's%20blend%20of%20disparate%20building%20types%20and%20architectural%20styles%20makes%20the%20city%20more%20visually%20interesting%20to%20pedestrians.%20There's%20even%20some%20evidence%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faeon.co%2Fessays%2Fwhy-boring-streets-make-pedestrians-stressed-and-unhappy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20variety%20is%20better%20for%20the%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%20of%20residents%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20who%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20get%20bored%20or%20depressed%20on%20their%20daily%20perambulations.%20But%20perhaps%20the%20most%20important%20benefit%20of%20Tokyo's%20flexible%20land-use%20rules%20is%20that%20they%20allow%20builders%20to%20quickly%20respond%20to%20changing%20demand%20and%20market%20pressures.%20No%20wonder%20Tokyo%20has%20stayed%20largely%20affordable%20even%20as%20other%20global%20cities%20have%20run%20into%20major%20supply%20crunches.%20In%20Japan%2C%20the%20average%20household%20spent%2011%25%20of%20its%20after-tax%20income%20on%20housing%20in%202022.%20Meanwhile%2C%20more%20than%2042%20million%20American%20households%20spent%20more%20than%20a%20third%20of%20their%20income%20on%20housing%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20number%20keeps%20climbing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20don't%20need%20to%20make%20every%20American%20city%20look%20like%20Tokyo%20to%20relieve%20our%20housing%20crisis%2C%20but%20we%20could%20learn%20from%20Japan's%20willingness%20to%20let%20developers%20and%20architects%20get%20a%20little%20weird.%20Some%20low-hanging%20fruit%20for%20building%20variability%20is%20right%20there%20in%20front%20of%20us%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EAllow%20the%20building%20of%20accessory%20dwelling%20units%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20More%20places%20can%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcayimby.org%2Freports%2Fcalifornia-adu-reform-a-retrospective%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efollow%20California's%20lead%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20allow%20the%20construction%20of%20ADUs%20%E2%80%94%20smaller%20homes%20that%20usually%20share%20a%20lot%20with%20a%20single-family%20structure.%20These%20small%20structures%20allow%20homeowners%20to%20add%20a%20small%20rental%20property%20in%20their%20backyard%20or%20a%20little%20garden%20apartment%20for%20a%20relative.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EAllow%20apartment%20buildings%20with%20one%20staircase%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Making%20it%20legal%20to%20build%20more%20apartment%20buildings%20with%20only%20one%20staircase%20would%20substantially%20reduce%20construction%20costs%20and%20allow%20for%20apartment%20buildings%20to%20be%20built%20on%20smaller%20lots.%20It%20would%20also%20lead%20to%20the%20construction%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niskanencenter.org%2Fhow-to-build-more-family-sized-apartments%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emore%20family-friendly%20apartments%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EStreamline%20outdated%20elevator%20codes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20As%20the%20building-codes%20guru%20Stephen%20Smith%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Building%20in%20North%20America%20recently%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F07%2F08%2Fopinion%2Felevator-construction-regulation-labor-immigration.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewrote%20for%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3Eelevators%20in%20the%20United%20States%20%26quot%3Bhave%20become%20over-engineered%2C%20bespoke%2C%20handcrafted%20and%20expensive%20pieces%20of%20equipment%20that%20are%20unaffordable%20in%20all%20the%20places%20where%20they%20are%20most%20needed.%26quot%3B%20Aligning%20American%20elevator%20codes%20with%20European%20standards%20would%20allow%20for%20smaller%2C%20cheaper%20elevators.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EEliminate%20minimum%20parking%20requirements%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Many%20cities%20require%20developers%20to%20include%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20off-street%20parking%20spots%20per%20housing%20unit%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they're%20building%20in%20a%20walkable%20area%20or%20near%20public%20transit%2C%20meaning%20residents%20wouldn't%20necessarily%20need%20to%20drive.%20Removing%20these%20mandates%20would%20allow%20developers%20to%20respond%20to%20market%20demand%20for%20parking%2C%20or%20lack%20thereof%2C%20and%20experiment%20with%20constructing%20parking-light%20or%20no-parking%20multifamily%20buildings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3ELegalize%20cohousing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20Boardinghouses%20and%20single-room-occupancy%20hotels%2C%20where%20residents%20had%20private%20bedrooms%20but%20potentially%20shared%20bathrooms%20and%20kitchens%2C%20used%20to%20be%20a%20common%2C%20naturally%20low-cost%20feature%20of%20many%20American%20cities.%20Now%20they're%20illegal%20in%20much%20of%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20except%20for%20some%20(frequently%20decrepit)%20SROs%20that%20were%20grandfathered%20in.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20short%2C%20more%20flexibility%20is%20good.%20More%20flexibility%20leads%20to%20more%20weird.%20People%20who%20really%20like%20single-family%20homes%20should%20still%20have%20access%20to%20single-family%20homes.%20But%20people%20who%20need%20a%20lower-cost%20option%2C%20like%20a%20micro-unit%20apartment%2C%20should%20have%20access%20to%20that%20option.%20Multigenerational%20households%20should%20have%20the%20choice%20to%20live%20in%20a%20